get adjacent post rel link "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==========================================================================

NAME
----

get adjacent post rel link - Get adjacent post relational link.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Get adjacent post relational link.

Can either be next or previous post relational link.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_adjacent_post_rel_link( $title, $in_same_cat, $excluded_categories, $previous ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$title` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Link title format.
    Default: %title

 `$in_same_cat` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Whether link should be in same category.
    Default: false

 `$excluded_categories` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Excluded categories IDs.
    Default: empty string

 `$previous` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional, default is true. Whether display link to
    previous post.
    Default: 1

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.8](/Version_2.8 "Version 2.8")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_adjacent_post_rel_link()` is located in
`wp-includes/link-template.php`

